veal a profound poet to a new generation of Anglophone readers while reacquainting Spanish readers with a stranger, more complicated “madwoman” than most have ever known.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh  amadwoman, crazy, women, gender, femininity, social roles, mental health, stigma, hysteria, sexuality, female author, latin america, literature, catastrophe, mourning, grief, loss, ballad, folk narrative, folklore, sanity, translation, poetry, abandonment, anxiety, ballerina, strength, fragility, beauty, humility, religion, imprisonment, clytemnestra, cassandra, mythology, electra, antigone, piety, bible.1 aCouch, Randall.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022653190840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226531892423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226531892/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles